I was very excited because this restaurant was open late, and after a long day of work I just wanted to cry into a bowl of thai fried rice. This place is located right next to two bars which is completely genius and I admire the plan. However. I ordered the Latenight Thai fried rice (it comes with shrimp and special sauce) and I was very excited to wait a moment for it. My order was ready and I walked up to the counter to recieve a plastic takeout container with an oddly orange rice in it. The vegetables and shrimp were without a doubt frozen and lacked all flavor. I'm not sure what the special sauce was but it was tolerable at best. I love thai food bit was really shocked at how far from thai fried rice this really was, i really wanted to like it. I do think that if you're famished at 2am and quite hammered, this will do

We love Thai food but this restaurant has no idea what the actual taste of Thailand really is.  Their Mongolian Chicken is dry and tasteless, while another chicken dish (Chicken Satay) was covered in oil.  I rather eat a day old fries then anything they make. My recommendation to anyone reading this - do not waste your $. And by the way, their packing is bad too. Everything was leaked by the time we got home.

My father and I went late at night hoping to find our new local late night spot to get some chow. We proceeded to enter the establishment but once at the counter we were unsure on how to order. We inquired on how to order but were saddened by their rude and sarcastic remark. Once we had ordered our food we realized that we were quite parched from our journey, and asked the young lady at the counter she simply pointed at the water cooler. My father fancied his water cold like the water of the Appalachian mountains so he made yet another perilous journey to ask the counter people for ice. Upon his arrival to the counter she asked is there anything else you would like very sarcastically. My father was livid at the fact that the staff was being so rude it almost seemed like they didn't want our business. So my father asked for the food to go once the meal was ready we got up to get and were given a dirty look upon taking it from the counter. We just ended up eating the food by our car although the only really redeeming experience was the food the sashimi and maki were pretty good as well as the fried rice.

WORST PLACE EVER!!! EVERYTHING IS MICROWAVED!! Pad Thai noodles were straight from the microwave. They literally came in the microwavable plastic container! Ordered for the first time from here and was very impressed. I work overnights at a nearby hospital so there's not many food options available. I do worry about ordering food for the first time due to past experiences but decided to give this place a try. I ordered the big pad Thai, miso soup,  and green tea bubble tea through postmates. Food was excellent and super filling. Delivery through postmates was also amazing as usual. I will definitely order from here again when I forget to bring my food from home for work. Highly recommend!

The store didn't accept cards so I tried to use their ATM. First problem is the max withdrawal I could take out is $20. Like you expect me to pay 3 service fees for my total bill? And not only that, I didn't get the cash! I told them about it, and I showed them on my phone that the cash withdrawal showed up on my bank account. Yet the guy, acting like it was no big deal, insisted that if I didn't get a receipt, that the withdrawal wouldn't go through. He then changes the box inside the ATM, and sure enough I saw 2 $20 bills still hanging off that box.  I found that to be pretty sketchy.  I still ordered food and I thought the pad Thai was amazing, and the crab ragoons were good, for how cheap they are.  I am not writing this review just because I got ripped off $20. I didn't like how he handled the situation, and as a customer, would rather try a better Thai service elsewhere in Chicago.

The food is ok for the affordable prices. If you want painfully spicy food, this will be the spot for you. My friend ordered the Tom Ka soup which did not have a spicy pepper logo next to it on the menu...however; it was way too spicy for anyone to enjoy, and they were not willing to make her a new soup or substitute it for something else. Also, the older man that works the counter had an unpleasant demeanor. They are also a "cash only" establishment with a broken atm.

My best friend and I went to the Lincoln Ave location on our way to a show at Lincoln Hall, we didn't have a whole lot of time but just enough to have some hot thai food on a freezing cold night. This place couldn't have been more perfect. The service was good, we didn't have to wait very long for anything that we ordered. We had an appetizer of steamed shrimp dumplings that were great. The Panang Curry was mild and thicker than I am used to, but had a good balance of the coconut milk base, curry, vegetables and tofu they used. My friend had the Massaman Curry with similar experience. Everything tasted great, though I could have used a little more thai basil as that was really what set my dish off. Not the absolute best Thai food in Chicago, but also not the most expensive place either. The prices were good and I had a very enjoyable experience and would definitely go back.

When my dish did come it was so spicy my lips where burning and guess what?! I didn't even order it spicy!! I went up to tell them nicely that this wasn't what I ordered (usually I hate complaining and even if my food isn't right I eat it anyway but this was UNBEARABLY hot! Coming from someone who does actually like spicy things this wasn't at all edible.) "The man who seemed like the manager said "too bad that's how it comes you can't get another one." I couldn't believe how rude and uncaring of my service they where! I asked him please sir I need something else my kid are burning. He said no. I couldn't get the dish I wanted in the first place and I couldn't get my money back. It's a waste of money for a small portion. $20 dollars for a plate that isn't even big enough to fill someone up and I can't even get it that way I'd like? They made a mistake and couldn't care less that it was wrong and a costumer was unhappy. Will never go there again they don't deserve any money.
